Dubbed Tanima Divers, the collection is the brainchild of Japanese designer Takayuki Fukusawa, head of EkoD Works (of Error Code Works).

He insists that he's trying to challenge 
the norms of society through his 'art', and says his life's goal is to 
create funny and playful designs that brighten people's days.

According to his design firm he wants to continue to create objects that make people say 'he made another ridiculous thing'.

The new range of cheeky pendants follow the firm's mantra, 'to make a world full of humorous art and design'.

