Last year Takayuki, 30, created his Delusion Mapping Project - a series of T-shirts with hyper realistic prints of women's bras.

Called the 'peek-a-boo', the printed tops aim to, in the words of the designer, 'bring to life the world of delusion that people secretly envision'.

'The time when our imaginings can be kept private in our minds has long passed. So, everyone don a delusion mapping t-shirt and jump into a new world of ambitious dreams!'

Sure to attract a giggle or lustful look if worn out in public, you can even chose a variety of colours for the bra underneath, and there are different breast shapes available - though all are a generous size.

